misconceptions.student_thought_process: The student understands the operational steps required to perform an array right shift with wrap-around: namely, saving the last element, shifting all other elements one place right starting from the end, and then placing the saved element at the start.
misconceptions.conceptual_gap: There is no conceptual gap present in the implementation logic itself. The student correctly applies iterative process control (loops and indexing) and temporary variable storage to achieve the desired transformation according to the Java execution model.
misconceptions.error_manifestation: None. The code produces the correct output for the specified task.
